<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-14T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="866" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Moose, James S./418: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-14T17:00:00-04:00">April 14,
                                    1943—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>536. Personal for the Minister. For your information the President
                            desires to appoint Mr. James S. Moose, Jr. to act as Minister Resident
                            to Saudi Arabia and has instructed the Legation at Jidda to request Mr.
                            Moose’s <hi rend="italic">agrément</hi>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>